#compdef config-lsp
# ============================================================================
# config-lsp - LSP server for system config files (Go, multi-license)
#
# Author : Myzel394
# Upstream: https://github.com/Myzel394/config-lsp
#
# config-lsp speaks the Language Server Protocol over stdio and
# provides editor completions + diagnostics + hover + go-to-
# definition for system config files that historically have had
# no formal schema or language tooling:
#
#   - /etc/ssh/sshd_config + /etc/ssh/ssh_config
#   - /etc/fstab
#   - /etc/hosts
#   - /etc/aliases (Postfix)
#   - /etc/gitconfig
#   - /etc/sudoers
#   - /etc/wireguard/*.conf
#   - many others
#
# The LSP lane is built on `github.com/tliron/glsp` (declared
# at upstream server/go.mod HEAD), the canonical Go LSP server
# library by Tal Liron (github.com/tliron/glsp, 270+ stars).
# glsp implements LSP 3.17 + the JSON-RPC 2.0 codec + Microsoft's
# Base Protocol framing (Content-Length + payload), with typed
# Go interfaces for the full LSP request + notification surface:
# initialize / didOpen / didChange / completion / hover / definition
# / references / diagnostics / workspaceSymbol / codeAction /
# executeCommand / semantic tokens / inlay hints / etc.
#
# config-lsp builds on top of glsp with per-file-type parsers
# (TextMate-style grammars for each config file's syntax) and
# a set of LSP root handlers that dispatch to the per-config
# language server based on URI patterns.
#
# Operator modes:
#   config-lsp           - run as LSP server over stdio
#   config-lsp --version - print version
#   config-lsp --help    - print help
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 216 :: LANGUAGE SERVER PROTOCOL (LSP 3.17, JSON-RPC 2.0)
# Round 1347 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 216
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : ebkalderon/tower-lsp              [R1346 _rime_ls]
#   Go      : tliron/glsp                       [R1347 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : microsoft/vscode-languageserver-node  [R1348 closing]
#
# config-lsp lands the "creative use of LSP" pattern visible in
# both lanes' openers: the Rust opener `rime_ls` uses LSP completion
# to surface Chinese input-method candidates; the Go middle
# `config-lsp` uses LSP completion to surface ssh_config /
# fstab / hosts directive names. Both treat the editor's
# completion popup as the universal UI for any "candidate
# string for the current cursor position" workflow, regardless
# of whether the original spec authors had code completion in
# mind for that use case.
# ============================================================================

_config-lsp() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help,help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)--version[print version]' \
        '(- *)version[print version]'
}

_config-lsp "$@"
